<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-07-18T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-07-18T07:00:00-05:00" n="717" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d717">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/615: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-07-18T14:00:00+02:00">July 18,
                                    1942—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 18—noon.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3975. Personal for the Secretary. Your message number 3272, July 15, 9
                            p.m. After making inquiry, I have decided it best to take this matter up
                            with Mr. Eden which I shall do on Monday. General Spears was Mr.
                            Churchill’s military contact officer with the French during the time
                            when Mr. Churchill was Prime Minister and the French nation was still
                            engaged on the European front. He is also an old personal friend.
                            Because of other matters that are under consideration here at this time,
                            I hope you will give me a little time to try to work out a satisfactory
                            solution.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>